Layer Responsibilities
Layer	Responsibility
dllmain	
DllMain
 → spawns 
InitThread
 → JvmWrapper::init() → ModuleManager::init() → Hooks::init() → wait for DELETE → cleanup → FreeLibraryAndExitThread
core/hooks	Gets wglSwapBuffers from opengl32.dll via GetProcAddress → hooks with MinHook → hooks WndProc via SetWindowLongPtr. The hooked SwapBuffers drives: 
beginFrame()
 → Menu::render() → ModuleManager::renderAll() → 
endFrame()
core/jvm_wrapper	Calls JNI_GetCreatedJavaVMs to find the JVM. Gets JVMTI environment. Scans loaded classes via JVMTI to find Forge's TransformingClassLoader. Bootstraps it for ClassLoader.loadClass() calls. Provides 
findClass()
, 
getMethodID()
, 
getFieldID()
 with JVMTI fallback.
config/mappings	Single header with all Minecraft class paths, method names, and JNI signatures.
sdk/	JNI wrappers for Minecraft objects. All methods use JvmWrapper::getEnv() internally — no JNIEnv* params.
modules/	Each feature inherits 
Module
 and implements 
onRender()
. ESP does all JNI reads AND drawing in the same 
onRender()
 call, wrapped in 
PushLocalFrame
/
PopLocalFrame
.
render/	Owns ImGui context. OpenGL3 backend with glPushAttrib/glPopAttrib for state preservation.
3 — DETAILED IMPLEMENTATION GUIDE
3.1 — DLL Entry Point (dllmain.cpp)
cpp
static DWORD WINAPI InitThread(LPVOID param) {
    AllocConsole(); freopen_s(..., "CONOUT$", "w", stdout);
    // 1. JvmWrapper::init()         — attach JVM + JVMTI + bootstrap classloader
    // 2. ModuleManager::init()      — cache JNI IDs (CMinecraft, CEntity, CWorld) + register modules
    // 3. Hooks::init()              — hook wglSwapBuffers + WndProc
    // 4. Loop: poll DELETE key
    // 5. Cleanup: ModuleManager::shutdown() → Hooks::shutdown() → JvmWrapper::shutdown()
    // 6. FreeLibraryAndExitThread
}
Key design rules:

All rendering and game-state reads happen inside the hooked wglSwapBuffers, never from the init thread.
JNI calls must happen on a thread attached to the JVM. The render thread must call 
AttachCurrentThreadAsDaemon
 if not already attached.
Use 
PushLocalFrame
 / 
PopLocalFrame
 for JNI local ref cleanup.
3.2 — JVM Wrapper with JVMTI (core/jvm_wrapper.cpp)
IMPORTANT

This is the most critical component. Incorrect class resolution causes silent failures — entities won't load, camera data won't resolve, and ESP will silently produce nothing.

3.2.1 — Initialization
cpp
bool JvmWrapper::init() {
    // 1. Find JVM
    jsize vmCount = 0;
    JNI_GetCreatedJavaVMs(&s_jvm, 1, &vmCount);
    if (!s_jvm) return false;
    // 2. Attach as daemon thread
    JNIEnv* env = nullptr;
    JavaVMAttachArgs args = { JNI_VERSION_1_8, "NullClient-Init", nullptr };
    s_jvm->AttachCurrentThreadAsDaemon((void**)&env, &args);
    // 3. Get JVMTI environment (critical for class discovery)
    s_jvm->GetEnv((void**)&s_jvmti, JVMTI_VERSION_1_0);
    // 4. Bootstrap Forge's classloader
    bootstrapClassLoader(env);
}
3.2.2 — Classloader Bootstrapping (THE KEY TO EVERYTHING)
Forge loads Minecraft classes with TransformingClassLoader, not the bootstrap classloader. Standard 
FindClass
 only searches the bootstrap classloader, so it fails for game classes. You must find and cache Forge's classloader:

cpp
void JvmWrapper::bootstrapClassLoader(JNIEnv* env) {
    // Use JVMTI GetLoadedClasses to scan ALL loaded classes
    jint classCount = 0;
    jclass* classes = nullptr;
    s_jvmti->GetLoadedClasses(&classCount, &classes);
    // Find Minecraft class to get its classloader
    for (jint i = 0; i < classCount; i++) {
        char* sig = nullptr;
        s_jvmti->GetClassSignature(classes[i], &sig, nullptr);
        if (sig && strcmp(sig, "Lnet/minecraft/client/Minecraft;") == 0) {
            // Get the classloader that loaded this class
            s_gameClassLoader = env->NewGlobalRef(env->CallObjectMethod(
                classes[i], env->GetMethodID(
                    env->FindClass("java/lang/Class"), "getClassLoader",
                    "()Ljava/lang/ClassLoader;")));
            // Cache ClassLoader.loadClass method
            jclass clClass = env->FindClass("java/lang/ClassLoader");
            s_loadClassMethod = env->GetMethodID(clClass, "loadClass",
                "(Ljava/lang/String;)Ljava/lang/Class;");
            break;
        }
        s_jvmti->Deallocate((unsigned char*)sig);
    }
    s_jvmti->Deallocate((unsigned char*)classes);
}
3.2.3 — Class Lookup (3-Tier Strategy)
cpp
jclass JvmWrapper::findClass(const char* name) {
    JNIEnv* env = getEnv();
    // Tier 1: Use bootstrapped classloader (most reliable for game classes)
    if (s_gameClassLoader && s_loadClassMethod) {
        // Convert "net/minecraft/client/Minecraft" → "net.minecraft.client.Minecraft"
        std::string dotName = name;
        std::replace(dotName.begin(), dotName.end(), '/', '.');
        jstring jname = env->NewStringUTF(dotName.c_str());
        jclass cls = (jclass)env->CallObjectMethod(s_gameClassLoader, s_loadClassMethod, jname);
        env->DeleteLocalRef(jname);
        if (cls && !env->ExceptionCheck()) {
            jclass globalRef = (jclass)env->NewGlobalRef(cls);
            env->DeleteLocalRef(cls);
            return globalRef;
        }
        if (env->ExceptionCheck()) env->ExceptionClear();
    }
    // Tier 2: Standard FindClass (works for java.* and system classes)
    jclass cls = env->FindClass(name);
    if (cls && !env->ExceptionCheck()) {
        jclass globalRef = (jclass)env->NewGlobalRef(cls);
        env->DeleteLocalRef(cls);
        return globalRef;
    }
    if (env->ExceptionCheck()) env->ExceptionClear();
    // Tier 3: JVMTI brute-force scan
    // ... scan all loaded classes for matching signature ...
    return nullptr;
}
3.2.4 — Method/Field Resolution with JVMTI Fallback
cpp
jmethodID JvmWrapper::getMethodID(jclass cls, const char* name, const char* sig) {
    JNIEnv* env = getEnv();
    // Try standard GetMethodID first
    jmethodID mid = env->GetMethodID(cls, name, sig);
    if (mid && !env->ExceptionCheck()) return mid;
    if (env->ExceptionCheck()) env->ExceptionClear();
    // Fallback: walk superclass chain (Forge may define methods on parent classes)
    jclass current = (jclass)env->NewLocalRef(cls);
    while (current) {
        mid = env->GetMethodID(current, name, sig);
        if (mid && !env->ExceptionCheck()) {
            env->DeleteLocalRef(current);
            return mid;
        }
        if (env->ExceptionCheck()) env->ExceptionClear();
        jclass super = env->GetSuperclass(current);
        env->DeleteLocalRef(current);
        current = super;
    }
    return nullptr;
}
3.2.5 — Thread Attachment
Every thread calling JNI must be attached. The render thread (wglSwapBuffers) is NOT the init thread:

cpp
JNIEnv* JvmWrapper::getEnv() {
    if (!s_jvm) return nullptr;
    JNIEnv* env = nullptr;
    jint result = s_jvm->GetEnv((void**)&env, JNI_VERSION_1_8);
    if (result == JNI_EDETACHED) {
        JavaVMAttachArgs args = { JNI_VERSION_1_8, "NullClient-Render", nullptr };
        s_jvm->AttachCurrentThreadAsDaemon((void**)&env, &args);
    }
    return env;
}
3.2.6 — Minimal JVMTI Header (jvmti_min.h)
You need a minimal JVMTI vtable header since the full JDK JVMTI header is huge. Define a struct with the correct vtable layout for GetLoadedClasses, 
GetClassSignature
, 
Deallocate
, and other needed functions. Match the vtable slot indices exactly.

3.3 — Hooking OpenGL wglSwapBuffers (core/hooks.cpp)
3.3.1 — Finding wglSwapBuffers
Much simpler than DX9 — it's an exported function:

cpp
bool Hooks::init() {
    MH_Initialize();
    HMODULE opengl = GetModuleHandleA("opengl32.dll");
    void* pSwapBuffers = (void*)GetProcAddress(opengl, "wglSwapBuffers");
    MH_CreateHook(pSwapBuffers, &hkWglSwapBuffers, (void**)&oWglSwapBuffers);
    MH_EnableHook(pSwapBuffers);
    return true;
}
3.3.2 — The Hooked wglSwapBuffers
cpp
BOOL WINAPI Hooks::hkWglSwapBuffers(HDC hdc) {
    // One-time init
    if (!s_initialized) {
        s_hwnd = WindowFromDC(hdc);
        if (s_hwnd) {
            oWndProc = (WNDPROC)SetWindowLongPtrA(s_hwnd, GWLP_WNDPROC, (LONG_PTR)hkWndProc);
            Renderer::init(s_hwnd);
            s_initialized = true;
        }
    }
    if (!s_initialized) return oWglSwapBuffers(hdc);
    // Render pipeline — NO separate tickAll/onUpdate step
    Renderer::beginFrame();
    Menu::render();
    ModuleManager::renderAll();  // ESP does its own JNI + drawing inside onRender
    Renderer::endFrame();
    return oWglSwapBuffers(hdc);
}
IMPORTANT

There is NO separate 
tickAll()
 step. Each module handles its own JNI inside 
onRender()
 with its own 
PushLocalFrame
/
PopLocalFrame
. This is critical because the JNI env must be valid during drawing.

3.4 — ImGui Initialization & Rendering (render/renderer.cpp)
3.4.1 — OpenGL3 Init
cpp
void Renderer::init(HWND hwnd) {
    IMGUI_CHECKVERSION();
    ImGui::CreateContext();
    ImGuiIO& io = ImGui::GetIO();
    io.ConfigFlags |= ImGuiConfigFlags_NavEnableKeyboard;
    io.IniFilename = nullptr;
    ImGui_ImplWin32_Init(hwnd);
    ImGui_ImplOpenGL3_Init("#version 130");
    setupStyle();
}
3.4.2 — Frame Lifecycle (OpenGL state preservation)
cpp
#include <GL/gl.h>  // For glPushAttrib/glPopAttrib only
void Renderer::beginFrame() {
    glPushAttrib(GL_ALL_ATTRIB_BITS);  // Save Minecraft's GL state
    ImGui_ImplOpenGL3_NewFrame();
    ImGui_ImplWin32_NewFrame();
    ImGui::NewFrame();
}
void Renderer::endFrame() {
    ImGui::EndFrame();
    ImGui::Render();
    ImGui_ImplOpenGL3_RenderDrawData(ImGui::GetDrawData());
    glPopAttrib();  // Restore Minecraft's GL state
}
WARNING

Do NOT include <GL/gl.h> in 
pch.h
 — it conflicts with ImGui's built-in OpenGL loader. Include it only locally in 
renderer.cpp
 where you need glPushAttrib/glPopAttrib.

WARNING

Do NOT define IMGUI_IMPL_OPENGL_LOADER_CUSTOM — let ImGui use its built-in loader for modern GL functions.

3.5 — SDK Layer — Minecraft JNI Wrappers (sdk/)
IMPORTANT

All SDK methods use JvmWrapper::getEnv() internally. Do NOT pass JNIEnv* as a parameter. This simplifies the API and ensures the correct env is always used.

3.5.1 — CMinecraft (sdk/minecraft.h)
cpp
class CMinecraft {
public:
    static bool initIDs();       // Uses JvmWrapper::findClass/getMethodID/getFieldID
    static jobject getInstance();// Read static 'instance' field OR call getInstance()
    static jobject getPlayer();  // mc.player field
    static jobject getWorld();   // mc.level field
    struct CameraData {
        double x, y, z;
        float  yaw, pitch, fov;
        int    screenW, screenH;
        bool   hasMatrices;
        float  viewMatrix[16], projMatrix[16];
        bool   valid;
    };
    static CameraData getCameraData();
};
getInstance() — Two strategies (try both):

cpp
jobject CMinecraft::getInstance() {
    JNIEnv* env = JvmWrapper::getEnv();
    // Strategy 1: Read static field 'instance' (most reliable in Forge)
    if (s_instanceField) {
        jobject mc = env->GetStaticObjectField(s_mcClass, s_instanceField);
        if (mc) return mc;
    }
    // Strategy 2: Call getInstance() method
    if (s_getInstance) {
        jobject mc = env->CallStaticObjectMethod(s_mcClass, s_getInstance);
        if (mc) return mc;
    }
    return nullptr;
}
getCameraData() — Camera uses FIELDS, not methods:

cpp
// Camera is NOT an Entity subclass. It stores position/rotation as FIELDS:
//   Camera.position → Vec3 field (read x, y, z as doubles)
//   Camera.yRot     → float field (yaw)
//   Camera.xRot     → float field (pitch)
// In initIDs():
s_camPosition = env->GetFieldID(cameraClass, "position", "Lnet/minecraft/world/phys/Vec3;");
s_camYRot = env->GetFieldID(cameraClass, "yRot", "F");
s_camXRot = env->GetFieldID(cameraClass, "xRot", "F");
// In getCameraData():
jobject camera = env->CallObjectMethod(gameRenderer, s_getMainCamera);
jobject pos = env->GetObjectField(camera, s_camPosition);  // Vec3 FIELD
data.x = env->GetDoubleField(pos, fx);
data.y = env->GetDoubleField(pos, fy);
data.z = env->GetDoubleField(pos, fz);
data.yaw   = env->GetFloatField(camera, s_camYRot);   // float FIELD
data.pitch = env->GetFloatField(camera, s_camXRot);   // float FIELD
Window — accessed as a FIELD on Minecraft, not via getWindow():

cpp
// In initIDs():
s_window = env->GetFieldID(mcClass, "window", "Lcom/mojang/blaze3d/platform/Window;");
s_getWidth  = env->GetMethodID(windowClass, "getWidth",  "()I");
s_getHeight = env->GetMethodID(windowClass, "getHeight", "()I");
// In getCameraData():
jobject window = env->GetObjectField(mc, s_window);  // FIELD access
data.screenW = env->CallIntMethod(window, s_getWidth);
data.screenH = env->CallIntMethod(window, s_getHeight);
FOV — read from Options.fov (OptionInstance<Integer>):

cpp
// Options.fov is an OptionInstance, call get() to get boxed Integer, then unbox
jobject opts = env->GetObjectField(mc, s_options);
jobject fovOpt = env->GetObjectField(opts, s_optFov);
jobject fovBoxed = env->CallObjectMethod(fovOpt, s_optInstGet);  // OptionInstance.get()
data.fov = (float)env->CallIntMethod(fovBoxed, intValueMethod);  // Integer.intValue()
Matrices — from RenderSystem static methods:

cpp
// RenderSystem.getProjectionMatrix() → Matrix4f (org/joml/Matrix4f)
// RenderSystem.getModelViewMatrix()  → Matrix4f
// Matrix4f has float fields: m00, m01, m02, m03, m10, m11, ... m33
// Read all 16 into float[16] arrays (column-major order)
3.5.2 — CEntity (sdk/entity.h)
cpp
class CEntity {
public:
    explicit CEntity(jobject obj) : m_obj(obj) {}
    bool isValid() const { return m_obj != nullptr; }
    // All use JvmWrapper::getEnv() internally
    double getX() const;
    double getY() const;
    double getZ() const;
    float  getYaw() const;     // Entity.getYRot()
    float  getPitch() const;   // Entity.getXRot()
    float  getHealth() const;  // LivingEntity.getHealth()
    float  getMaxHealth() const;
    int    getId() const;
    bool   isAlive() const;
    bool   isLiving() const;   // env->IsInstanceOf(m_obj, s_livingClass)
    bool   isPlayer() const;   // env->IsInstanceOf(m_obj, s_playerClass)
    bool   isItem() const;     // env->IsInstanceOf(m_obj, s_itemClass)
    std::string getName() const;
    struct AABB { double minX, minY, minZ, maxX, maxY, maxZ; };
    AABB getBoundingBox() const;
    static bool initIDs();  // Uses JvmWrapper::findClass etc.
private:
    jobject m_obj;
    static inline jclass s_entityClass, s_livingClass, s_playerClass, s_itemClass;
    static inline jmethodID s_getX, s_getY, s_getZ, s_getHealth, s_getMaxHealth;
    // ... all cached IDs
};
3.5.3 — CWorld (sdk/world.h)
cpp
class CWorld {
public:
    static bool initIDs();
    static std::vector<CEntity> getPlayers(jobject worldObj);
    static std::vector<CEntity> getAllEntities(jobject worldObj);  // NO env param
};
// getAllEntities uses entitiesForRendering() → Iterable → Iterator pattern
std::vector<CEntity> CWorld::getAllEntities(jobject worldObj) {
    JNIEnv* env = JvmWrapper::getEnv();
    jobject iterable = env->CallObjectMethod(worldObj, s_entitiesForRendering);
    jobject iterator = env->CallObjectMethod(iterable, s_iterator);
    std::vector<CEntity> result;
    while (env->CallBooleanMethod(iterator, s_hasNext)) {
        jobject entity = env->CallObjectMethod(iterator, s_next);
        if (entity) result.emplace_back(entity);
    }
    // cleanup local refs...
    return result;
}
3.6 — Module System (modules/)
3.6.1 — Base Class
cpp
class Module {
public:
    Module(const std::string& name, int keyBind);
    virtual ~Module() = default;
    virtual void onEnable() {}
    virtual void onDisable() {}
    virtual void onRender() {}   // ALL module logic goes here (JNI reads + drawing)
    // NO onUpdate(JNIEnv*) — modules manage their own JNI in onRender()
    void toggle();
    void setEnabled(bool v);
    bool isEnabled() const;
protected:
    bool m_enabled = false;
    std::unordered_map<std::string, float>  m_floatSettings;
    std::unordered_map<std::string, bool>   m_boolSettings;
    std::unordered_map<std::string, ImVec4> m_colorSettings;
};
3.6.2 — Module Manager
cpp
class ModuleManager {
public:
    static void init();         // NO env param — uses JvmWrapper internally
    static void shutdown();
    static void renderAll();    // Calls onRender() on enabled modules
    static void handleKey(int vk);
    static Module* getModule(const std::string& name);
};
3.7 — EspRenderer — WorldToScreen (render/esp_renderer.h)
EspRenderer is a CLASS with static camera state. 
worldToScreen
 takes world coordinates and subtracts camera position internally:

cpp
class EspRenderer {
public:
    // Call once per frame
    static void updateCamera(double camX, double camY, double camZ,
                             float yaw, float pitch, int screenW, int screenH);
    static void setFOV(float fov);
    static void setMatrices(bool hasMatrices, const float* view, const float* proj);
    // Project WORLD coordinates to screen (subtracts camera internally)
    static bool worldToScreen(double x, double y, double z, ImVec2& out);
    // Draw all ESP elements for one entity
    struct EspColors { ImU32 boxVisible, boxHidden, text; };
    static void drawEntity(const CEntity& entity, bool drawBox, bool drawName,
                           bool drawHealth, bool drawDistance, const EspColors& colors);
private:
    static inline double s_camX, s_camY, s_camZ;
    static inline float  s_yaw, s_pitch, s_fov = 70.0f;
    static inline int    s_screenW = 1920, s_screenH = 1080;
    static inline bool   s_hasMatrices = false;
    static inline float  s_viewMatrix[16], s_projMatrix[16];
};
3.7.1 — WorldToScreen (Matrix-Based Primary)
cpp
bool EspRenderer::worldToScreen(double x, double y, double z, ImVec2& out) {
    double dx = x - s_camX, dy = y - s_camY, dz = z - s_camZ;
    if (s_hasMatrices) {
        // View transform: vec4 = (dx, dy, dz, 1.0) × viewMatrix
        double clipX = dx*s_viewMatrix[0] + dy*s_viewMatrix[4] + dz*s_viewMatrix[8]  + s_viewMatrix[12];
        double clipY = dx*s_viewMatrix[1] + dy*s_viewMatrix[5] + dz*s_viewMatrix[9]  + s_viewMatrix[13];
        double clipZ = dx*s_viewMatrix[2] + dy*s_viewMatrix[6] + dz*s_viewMatrix[10] + s_viewMatrix[14];
        double clipW = dx*s_viewMatrix[3] + dy*s_viewMatrix[7] + dz*s_viewMatrix[11] + s_viewMatrix[15];
        // Projection transform
        double ndcX = clipX*s_projMatrix[0] + clipY*s_projMatrix[4] + clipZ*s_projMatrix[8]  + clipW*s_projMatrix[12];
        double ndcY = clipX*s_projMatrix[1] + clipY*s_projMatrix[5] + clipZ*s_projMatrix[9]  + clipW*s_projMatrix[13];
        double ndcW = clipX*s_projMatrix[3] + clipY*s_projMatrix[7] + clipZ*s_projMatrix[11] + clipW*s_projMatrix[15];
        if (ndcW < 0.1) return false;
        out.x = (float)((ndcX/ndcW * 0.5 + 0.5) * s_screenW);
        out.y = (float)((1.0 - (ndcY/ndcW * 0.5 + 0.5)) * s_screenH);
        return true;
    }
    // Fallback: trigonometry (when matrices unavailable)
    // ... yaw/pitch rotation to view space, perspective divide with FOV ...
}
3.7.2 — drawEntity
drawEntity
 gets the AABB from the entity, projects all 8 corners, computes enclosing 2D rect, draws box/name/health/distance. This keeps drawing logic out of the ESP module.

3.8 — ESP Module (modules/esp.cpp)
IMPORTANT

ESP does ALL JNI reads AND drawing in 
onRender()
. It calls 
PushLocalFrame(256)
 at the start and 
PopLocalFrame(nullptr)
 at the end. There is no separate 
onUpdate()
 phase.

cpp
class ESP : public Module {
public:
    ESP() : Module("ESP", 0) {
        m_enabled = true;  // On by default
        m_boolSettings["draw_boxes"] = true;
        m_boolSettings["draw_names"] = true;
        m_boolSettings["draw_health"] = true;
        m_boolSettings["draw_distance"] = true;
        m_boolSettings["draw_animals"] = false;
        m_boolSettings["draw_items"] = false;
        m_floatSettings["max_distance"] = 200.0f;
        m_colorSettings["box_visible"] = ImVec4(0.55f, 0.40f, 1.00f, 0.80f);
        m_colorSettings["text_color"]  = ImVec4(1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f, 1.0f);
    }
    void onRender() override;   // Only override — no onUpdate
};
3.8.1 — ESP::onRender() Flow
1.  if (!m_enabled) return;
2.  env = JvmWrapper::getEnv(); if (!env) return;
3.  env->PushLocalFrame(256);
4.  localPlayer = CMinecraft::getPlayer();  // no env param
5.  camData = CMinecraft::getCameraData();  // no env param
6.  EspRenderer::setFOV(camData.fov);
7.  EspRenderer::setMatrices(camData.hasMatrices, ...);
8.  screenW/H from camData or fallback to ImGui DisplaySize
9.  EspRenderer::updateCamera(camX, camY, camZ, yaw, pitch, screenW, screenH);
10. worldObj = CMinecraft::getWorld();
11. entities = CWorld::getAllEntities(worldObj);  // no env param
12. For each entity:
    a. Skip self (getId match)
    b. Skip dead (!isAlive)
    c. Categorize: isPlayer, isLiving, isItem
    d. Apply category filters
    e. Distance check
    f. Color-code by type
    g. EspRenderer::drawEntity(entity, boxes, names, health, distance, colors);
13. env->PopLocalFrame(nullptr);
