3.10 — Build System (CMakeLists.txt)
cmake
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.20)
project(Overlay LANGUAGES CXX)
set(CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD 20)
add_subdirectory(minhook)
set(IMGUI_DIR "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/imgui")
set(IMGUI_SOURCES
    ${IMGUI_DIR}/imgui.cpp ${IMGUI_DIR}/imgui_draw.cpp
    ${IMGUI_DIR}/imgui_tables.cpp ${IMGUI_DIR}/imgui_widgets.cpp
    ${IMGUI_DIR}/imgui_demo.cpp
    ${IMGUI_DIR}/backends/imgui_impl_opengl3.cpp
    ${IMGUI_DIR}/backends/imgui_impl_win32.cpp
)
file(GLOB_RECURSE PROJECT_SOURCES "src/*.cpp")
add_library(overlay SHARED ${PROJECT_SOURCES} ${IMGUI_SOURCES})
target_include_directories(overlay PRIVATE
    ${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/src ${IMGUI_DIR} ${IMGUI_DIR}/backends
)
target_link_libraries(overlay PRIVATE minhook opengl32)
target_compile_definitions(overlay PRIVATE WIN32_LEAN_AND_MEAN NOMINMAX _CRT_SECURE_NO_WARNINGS)
WARNING

Link opengl32 NOT d3d9. Do NOT add IMGUI_IMPL_OPENGL_LOADER_CUSTOM — let ImGui use its built-in loader.

4 — CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
JVMTI is mandatory. Without JVMTI classloader bootstrapping, 
FindClass
 will fail for all Minecraft classes under Forge. This is the single most important requirement.

Camera uses FIELDS not methods. Camera.position is a 
Vec3
 field. Camera.yRot and Camera.xRot are float fields. Do NOT try to call getPosition() or getYRot() methods — they may not exist.

Window is a FIELD. Access Minecraft.window as a field, not via getWindow() method. The class is com/mojang/blaze3d/platform/Window.

No separate onUpdate/tickAll pattern. The ESP module does its JNI reads AND drawing inside 
onRender()
, wrapped in 
PushLocalFrame
/
PopLocalFrame
. Do NOT split JNI work into a separate 
onUpdate(JNIEnv*)
 method.

SDK methods take no JNIEnv* param. All SDK classes (
CMinecraft
, 
CWorld
, 
CEntity
) call JvmWrapper::getEnv() internally.

OpenGL state preservation. Use glPushAttrib(GL_ALL_ATTRIB_BITS) / glPopAttrib() around ImGui rendering in the SwapBuffers hook to avoid corrupting Minecraft's GL state.

Do NOT include <GL/gl.h> in pch.h. It conflicts with ImGui's built-in OpenGL3 loader. Include it only locally where needed (e.g., 
renderer.cpp
).

AttachCurrentThreadAsDaemon, not 
AttachCurrentThread
, to avoid preventing JVM shutdown.

Exception handling: After every JNI call that could fail, check env->ExceptionCheck() and clear with env->ExceptionClear(). Silent exceptions will corrupt subsequent JNI calls.

Minecraft singleton in Forge may be stored as a static FIELD called instance rather than being accessible via a static method 
getInstance()
. Try the field first, method second.

5 — SUMMARY CHECKLIST
 DLL injects and init thread runs
 JVMTI environment acquired, Forge classloader bootstrapped
 All Minecraft classes found via ClassLoader.loadClass()
 wglSwapBuffers hook fires every frame
 ImGui renders on top of Minecraft without corrupting GL state
 INSERT toggles the menu; mouse captured when menu open
 DELETE cleanly unloads DLL
 ESP draws 2D boxes around entities
 Health bars show green→yellow→red gradient
 Names centered above box with dark background
 Distance labels below box
 Self (local player) filtered out
 Dead entities filtered
 Distance filter respects slider
 W2S handles behind-camera correctly (returns false)
This prompt is self-contained. An AI given this document plus the ImGui and MinHook libraries should produce a complete, compilable OpenGL overlay + ESP project that works with Minecraft Forge 1.21.1.